{"type":"message","id":"db4d5bce","parentId":"f871b7af","timestamp":"2026-05-13T02:12:18.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at this more carefully, it seems the pipeline executed the steps. The \"上传CDN\" step completed. But I notice there's no \"start\" line for the pipeline steps I can easily find. Let me check if there were any errors or if everything went fine.\n\nThe exit code is 0, which means Unity completed without a hard error. The 404 on downloading Server.json template is non-fatal since it created one locally.\n\nAlso I noticed the `RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat` from `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\` uses `2020.3.49f1` (without `c1`), which matches what I used. So that bat file would work.\n\nBut there's a concern - the `ServerConfigTemplate_Test.json` doesn't exist. Let me check if it's supposed to be something else.\n\nActually wait, looking at the log again at line 683488:\n```\nSystem.Net.WebException: The remote server returned an error: (404) Not Found.\n```\nThis was from `DownloadCDNFile` which downloads from a URL, not from a local file. The local file check with `Test-Path` returning `False` is because `ServerConfigTemplate_Test.json` doesn't exist - it was trying to download it as a template from CDN.\n\nLooking at the pipeline steps, it seems to have:\n1. Set up local test environment\n2. Upload to CDN (completed in 1.475s)\n3. The test environment is at `D:/cdn_solo\\update\\Android\\Test1\\1.0.41`\n\nOverall the pipeline completed successfully despite the 404 warning. This seems like it completed the hot update process.\n\nLet me now send a summary to the channel.\n\nWait, actually looking at the log more carefully at the \"end 'Excute Pipline:上传CDN'\" line, the time is 1.475s which is very short. Let me check for the start time of the pipeline too.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_o6x290i7BAzAJRG33xyE0956","name":"exec","arguments":{"com